oai_dc:dc.dc:title: ACETYLENIC DERIVATIVES OF [FE2(CO)6(MU-SE2)] - ACETYLENIC BOND REDUCTION ON A SELENIUM-STABILIZED FE2PT MIXED-METAL COMPLEX
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: MATHUR, P
HOSSAIN, MM
DAS, K
SINHA, UC

oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Stepwise addition of phenylacetylene and Pt(PPh3)2 across the Se-Se bond of [Fe2(CO)6(mu-Se2)] can be carried out at room temperature; X-ray analysis demonstrates the acetylenic carbon-carbon bond reduction in the mixed-metal complex [(CO)6Fe2Pt(PPh3)2{mu-SeC(Ph)C(H)Se}].
